snippet.title: HybridAuth
snippet.description: HybridAuth enable developers to easily build social applications to engage websites vistors and customers on a social level by implementing social signin, social sharing, users profiles, friends list, activities stream, status updates and more. HybridAuth goal is to act as an abstract api between your application and various social apis and identities providers such as Facebook, Twitter, MySpace and Google.

snippet.title: NFSP
snippet.description: NFSP implements a distributed nfsv2 server - it is heavily based on the user mode nfs daemon. A node is chosen to act as server of metadata, other nodes have to be chosen to be I/O nodes. Every other node (but the metadata sever) may be a client.

snippet.title: SNMP Simulator
snippet.description: SNMP Simulator is a software that would act like a multitude of real physical devices from SNMP Manager's point of view. Simulator builds and uses a database of physical devices' SNMP footprints to respond like their real counterparts do.

snippet.title: YuiAI
snippet.description: YuiAI is meant to be an AI assistant used to help you in your day to day activities. At first download she will more than likely act and behave as a simple child would, but over time will hopefully learn the tasks that you do from day to day. This is a personal side project and I do not know how long it will last, but would love to see it to grow.
